To avoid the stack overflow error with large input you would have to rewrite it to a loop. For example using a while loop:
```java
    static double logbase2(double x) {
        double acc = 0;
        double temp = x;
        while (temp &gt; 1) {
            temp /= 2;
            acc += 1;
        }
        return acc;
    }
```
JVM does not support the tail call optimisation unfortunately (although in scala or kotlin you can write recursive functions with tail calls and during the compilation those will be rewritten to loops). 
If a a TCO would work in Java you would be able to write something like this:
```java
    static double logbase2Acc(double x, double acc) {// It calculates Log base 2 n
        if (x &lt;= 1)
            return acc;
        else
            return logbase2Acc(x / 2, acc + 1);
    }
```

